Snowden ready to “cooperate” with Germany on US surveillance issue
Edward Snowden, the whistleblower for U.S. intelligence services, said he was willing to travel to Berlin to testify before the German parliament if the U.S. National Security Agency and its director Keith Alexander did not provide answers about their activities.
German MP Hans-Christian Str<0xC3><0xB6>bele met on Thursday with Mr Snowden in Russia, where he enjoys the right of asylum, to discuss his testimony in Germany.
